<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1587" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1587">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 723.2515/272.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister to Peru</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Nov. 12, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Department has been informed by Legation at Santiago and Chilean
                            Minister here that an agreement has been effected for reestablishment of
                            diplomatic relations between Peru and Chile and the settlement of
                            Tacna-Arica question. Has Peruvian Government officially informed you of
                            the conclusion of such an arrangement so full of promise for the future
                            welfare of both countries? What are the probabilities for its
                            ratification by Peruvian Congress?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>